<br>
Total: 90    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> The hole idea of your companions smoking weed to heal was simply too cool. I had to make this deck.<br>
<br>
There aren&#39;t many hidden combo&#39;s in this deck. It&#39;s very basic. In the start take it easy and build up your fellowship, play some pipeweed possesions and wait for the pipes to arrive. When they do you&#39;re ready to rock: discard the pipeweed possesions to heal your companions and then shuffle them back into the deck by exerting Bilbo (who heals every turn because of Frodo). Combined with Legolas and Aragorn with his bow you can shoot multiple times each turn making it easier to run. A Ranger&#39;s Versatility helps you shoot down more minions. <br>
<br>
The shadow side is even more simple than the free peoples&#39;: Armories to make points, cheap moria orcs with weapons to swarm him, and occasionally the Cave Troll joins in on the party to beat a few companions. The Goblin Swarms make sure your orcs come back each turn.   <br>
<br>
You&#39;re maybe thinking that the free people&#39;s side will take forever to get up and running because it needs a lot of cards. But it doesn&#39;t. You normally get the cards you need pretty fast because this deck draws lots of cards because most of the cards are possesions, conditions and companions/minions so you can play them right away and draw new cards afterwards. Cards like &quot;Delving&quot; and Elrond helps speeding up the process. Normally your fellowship will be ready to rock at the same time as your shadow deck: At site 4.<br>
<br>
The sites:<br>
[1]: Aragorn is important in this deck so if I start I would love to play him from deck.<br>
[2]: It&#39;s a forest (ARV) and stealth events pisses me off.<br>
[3]: It&#39;s a forest. No more reason I hardly use it&#39;s game text. Actually I&#39;m thinking of replacing it with the &quot;Council Courtyard&quot; because my minions don&#39;t need that many shadow points, hopefully his does:)<br>
[4]: Ten hand weapons in my shadow deck makes this a niiiiice site. <br>
[5]: It&#39;s simply the best site 5 there is:)<br>
[6]: The first orc I play is costs -2.<br>
[7]: The only real option I had, though I have thought of playing with &quot;Anduin Wilderland&quot; instead because no archery phase means swarm time. (but the sam thing goes for my free peoples&#39; side).<br>
[8]: I always (almost) stop him here.<br>
[9]: Well none of the sites appeal to me but this one is the only one I have a chance of using (&quot;Goblin Patrol Troop&quot;, &quot;Guard Commander&quot; and &quot;Moria Scout&quot; can become fierce, but this requires that he has no archery to use).<br>
<br>
I would just like to say that this deck is made for fun, but it can surely kick ass.<br>
I&#39;m sure it has already been made by someone else. In that case I can&#39;t take credit for it but I haven&#39;t seen other decks like this yet (maybe because it&#39;s my second day at decktech).<br>
<br>
